cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about a toolkit for neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of the standard attention-based encoder-decoder framework, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The toolkit is built on top of Theano, a popular deep learning framework, which is also used in other subfields such as neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
